# Oracle to Odoo Migration Case Studies from Saudi Arabian Client

Odoo migration case studies from **Oracle ERP systems** (EBS, E‑Business Suite, and legacy Oracle‑based ERPs) are increasingly common as companies look to reduce licensing costs, modernize workflows, and gain flexibility. Below is a concise synthesis of real‑world Oracle‑to‑Odoo migration examples and patterns you can reference for your **odooupgradeservice.com** content and sales messaging.

## 1. Saudi‑based company: Oracle → Odoo (cost‑reduction case)

**Source:** NITI / LinkedIn case‑style post on ERP cost reduction. [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/accurate-management-system_erp-costs-often-increase-over-time-without-activity-7409087968759414784-Mqic)

**Context**
- A Saudi organization was running an Oracle‑based ERP (likely Oracle EBS or a custom Oracle ERP) with:
  - High licensing and maintenance fees.
  - Opaque cost structures.
  - Limited user adoption and rigid workflows.
- The business wanted to **reduce ERP costs materially** without losing core functionality.

**Migration approach**
- Partnered with an Odoo migration consultant to:
  - Analyze existing Oracle modules and workflows.
  - Map Oracle data models to Odoo equivalents (finance, inventory, sales, HR, etc.).
  - Migrate master data (partners, products, chart of accounts) and a limited set of transaction history to keep the odoo database clean. [brainvire](https://www.brainvire.com/odoo-erp-migration/)
- Used a phased method:
  - Test migration in staging.
  - UAT with key users.
  - Controlled cutover during a low‑activity window. [aaravsolutions](https://www.aaravsolutions.com/how-does-data-migration-work-in-erp-a-step-by-step-odoo-implementation-guide/)

**Outcomes**
- Reported **reduction in ERP costs by approximately 90%** (license‑heavy Oracle stack replaced with Odoo Community/Enterprise subscription model). [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/accurate-management-system_erp-costs-often-increase-over-time-without-activity-7409087968759414784-Mqic)
- Improved **operational visibility** and **user experience** due to Odoo’s intuitive UI and web‑based access. [brainvire](https://www.brainvire.com/odoo-erp-migration/)
- Gained ability to **customize and extend** Odoo modules much more easily than Oracle. [entrivistech](https://www.entrivistech.com/blog/odoo-1/upgrade-to-odoo-erp-as-oracle-legacy-systems-phase-out-58)

**Key lesson**
Oracle‑to‑Odoo migrations are often driven by **cost control and simplicity**, especially in GCC‑style license‑heavy environments.


## 2. Oracle EBS / legacy Oracle ERP → Odoo (consultant‑style reference)

**Sources:** ERP‑migration‑guide materials and Oracle‑to‑Odoo service pages. [sysgenpro](https://sysgenpro.com/resources/oracle-to-odoo-erp-migration-explained)

**Context**
- A mid‑sized manufacturer or distribution company running Oracle EBS or a custom Oracle ERP wanted:
  - Lower total cost of ownership.
  - Easier customization and integration.
  - A cloud‑ready, modular ERP.

**Migration approach**
- **Assessment phase**:
  - Deep dive into existing Oracle configuration, data model, and customizations.
  - Identify which modules to migrate (finance, inventory, sales, procurement) and which processes to refactor. [entrivistech](https://www.entrivistech.com/blog/odoo-1/upgrade-to-odoo-erp-as-oracle-legacy-systems-phase-out-58)
- **Data migration**:
  - Extract data from Oracle (via SQL or ETL tools).
  - Cleanse and transform it (remove duplicates, fix currency/date formats, reconcile balances).
  - Load into Odoo via CSV imports or migration scripts, often in a **staging DB first**. [newsroompanama](https://newsroompanama.com/2025/12/23/understanding-odoo-migration-a-complete-guide-to-erp-upgrades-and-data-transfer/)
- **Module and workflow mapping**:
  - Rebuild core Oracle workflows using Odoo apps (e.g., `account`, `stock`, `purchase`, `sale`).
  - Add custom modules or third‑party apps where Oracle had specialized features. [newsroompanama](https://newsroompanama.com/2025/12/23/understanding-odoo-migration-a-complete-guide-to-erp-upgrades-and-data-transfer/)

**Outcomes**
- **Lower ongoing licensing and support costs** compared with Oracle‑based systems. [sysgenpro](https://sysgenpro.com/resources/oracle-to-odoo-erp-migration-explained)
- **Improved agility**: faster deployment of new features and integrations (e‑commerce, HR, mobile). [brainvire](https://www.brainvire.com/odoo-erp-migration/)
- **Simplified maintenance** and better alignment with modern DevOps and hosting practices. [sysgenpro](https://sysgenpro.com/resources/oracle-to-odoo-erp-migration-explained)

**Key lesson**
Successfully replacing Oracle EBS‑style ERP with Odoo requires **not just data migration, but a rethink of business processes** and use of Odoo’s modular design.


