## 4. How Oracle‑to‑Odoo migration is typically described

Across migration‑guides and service providers, Oracle‑to‑Odoo projects follow a standard pattern: [entrivistech](https://www.entrivistech.com/blog/odoo-1/upgrade-to-odoo-erp-as-oracle-legacy-systems-phase-out-58)

### Drivers to move from Oracle to Odoo
- **High licensing and support costs** of Oracle EBS / legacy Oracle ERP. [sysgenpro](https://sysgenpro.com/resources/oracle-to-odoo-erp-migration-explained)
- **Rigid architecture** and slow change cycles compared with Odoo’s modular apps and frequent updates. [newsroompanama](https://newsroompanama.com/2025/12/23/understanding-odoo-migration-a-complete-guide-to-erp-upgrades-and-data-transfer/)
- Need for **cloud‑ready, web‑based** ERP with better UX and mobility. [entrivistech](https://www.entrivistech.com/blog/odoo-1/upgrade-to-odoo-erp-as-oracle-legacy-systems-phase-out-58)

### Usual migration steps
1. **System assessment**  
   - Inventory modules, customizations, and interfaces in Oracle. [brainvire](https://www.brainvire.com/odoo-erp-migration/)
2. **Business‑process mapping**  
   - Map Oracle workflows to Odoo modules (finance, inventory, sales, HR, project, manufacturing). [brainvire](https://www.brainvire.com/odoo-erp-migration/)
3. **Data migration strategy**  
   - Decide which data to migrate (full history vs recent).
   - Extract, cleanse, and map fields (e.g., Oracle GL to Odoo accounting). [aaravsolutions](https://www.aaravsolutions.com/how-does-data-migration-work-in-erp-a-step-by-step-odoo-implementation-guide/)
4. **Test migration and UAT**  
   - Run at least one full test migration in staging (data + workflows). [aaravsolutions](https://www.aaravsolutions.com/how-does-data-migration-work-in-erp-a-step-by-step-odoo-implementation-guide/)
5. **Go‑live and hypercare**  
   - Final cutover, 24–76 hour monitoring, and user support. [newsroompanama](https://newsroompanama.com/2025/12/23/understanding-odoo-migration-a-complete-guide-to-erp-upgrades-and-data-transfer/)

### Typical timelines
- Small to mid‑sized Oracle migrations: **2–4 months** depending on complexity and data volume. [sysgenpro](https://sysgenpro.com/resources/oracle-to-odoo-erp-migration-explained)
- Larger, multi‑company, multi‑module setups: **4–8 months** with phased rollouts. [entrivistech](https://www.entrivistech.com/blog/odoo-1/upgrade-to-odoo-erp-as-oracle-legacy-systems-phase-out-58)


## 5. Tools and methods commonly used

When moving from Oracle databases to Odoo, implementors often combine:

- **Direct SQL / ETL extraction** from Oracle DB. [aaravsolutions](https://www.aaravsolutions.com/how-does-data-migration-work-in-erp-a-step-by-step-odoo-implementation-guide/)
- **ETL and scripting tools** (e.g., Talend, Pentaho, or custom Python scripts) to transform data into Odoo‑friendly formats. [arbisoft](https://arbisoft.com/blogs/how-to-migrate-to-odoo-from-net-suite-a-detailed-guide)
- **Odoo internal tools**:
  - CSV import UI.
  - Custom migration modules or scripts (e.g., Odoo‑side Python jobs that call `create` and `write` for records). [brainvire](https://www.brainvire.com/odoo-erp-migration/)

Odoo partners explicitly mention **Oracle‑to‑Odoo migration** as a core service, including data‑mapping, process‑re‑design, and post‑go‑live optimization. [newsroompanama](https://newsroompanama.com/2025/12/23/understanding-odoo-migration-a-complete-guide-to-erp-upgrades-and-data-transfer/)


